author: By Arlene Fleming
title: TSA Airport Security Videos - Videos about Airport Security Screening from TSA
text:
The TSA has added 4 more informational videos for holiday travelers. Even if you aren't flying during the holidays, or through an airport in the United States, these tips for airport security screening points are pretty helpful.
Three Simple Steps - basics of getting through airport security screening points.
Laptops and Electronics - having your laptops and electronics out of your carry on and ready for inspection (not required at all airports outside the United States).
Choose Your Lane - there are different security lane options available to travelers - expert, casual or family/medical liquids.
Traveling with Children - know what you can bring through security and how to prep for it when you have extra items like car seats.
